[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Troubleshooting NPE Issue**\n\nI need to resolve a null pointer exception (NPE) related to CONFIG.links. It seems like the command line option for linking isn't setting CONFIG.links properly, even though it might be coded for plural options. I'm questioning the parsing for --link, as it might not be initializing CONFIG.links, leading to issues in the getLinkAnchor function. There’s something off in how options.links is being interpreted. I’ll have to dig deeper into this usage to find the root cause.\n\n**Analyzing Link Syntax Issue**\n\nI’m trying to figure out the correct syntax for the '--link' option, as the combined argument 'java.=url' might be causing confusion. The expectation for two arguments (prefixes and URL) seems off since I've passed it as one. Also, the code checks options.links instead of options.link, which might be an issue. I'm considering exploring Groovy CLI for clarity but can't run the tests right now. I might need to think about using different return types to avoid a null pointer exception (NPE) that stems from my parameter handling.\n\n**Investigating NPE in String Method**\n\nI’m looking into the String receiver method, which has only the first parameter and no additional ones. In this case, the parametersDocUrl could be empty, and it should return void. It seems that a comment link to java.util.List is what triggers the getLinkAnchor execution, leading to a null pointer exception (NPE). I need to consider using only GDK links since those aren't checking CONFIG.links, and also think about scenarios where there’s no package return.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06516fb98aa643c7016a0032b96f38819782386faa1e314682\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqADLFBPXQj13KiN-m-P2ulGUzo1U6MzLNjVZoAph3CMon7XsdUbWD9gMbBoOW0m6myl5j0-2qPFpyjZ6RiqaQnNW_FNp3FFoMRC2fkk4E0K3UoADjtzj9Gd6mnZ1oLIKv1kXa2SJ3V4oHOPfswkchH2IsFxeGm4